# Import necessary libraries
import pandas as pd
import numpy as np
from google.colab import files
import statsmodels.api as sm
from statsmodels.tsa.stattools import adfuller, coint
from statsmodels.tsa.arima.model import ARIMA
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# Upload files
print("Please upload NVDA.xlsx")
uploaded_nvda = files.upload()
print("Please upload MSFT.xlsx")
uploaded_msft = files.upload()

# Read Excel files
nvda_df = pd.read_excel('NVDA.xlsx')
msft_df = pd.read_excel('MSFT.xlsx')

# Extract PRICE columns and ensure they're numeric
nvda_prices = pd.to_numeric(nvda_df['PRICE'], errors='coerce')
msft_prices = pd.to_numeric(msft_df['PRICE'], errors='coerce')

# Drop any NaN values
nvda_prices = nvda_prices.dropna()
msft_prices = msft_prices.dropna()

# Function to perform ADF test
def adf_test(series, title=''):
    print(f'\nAugmented Dickey-Fuller Test: {title}')
    result = adfuller(series, autolag='AIC')
    print(f'ADF Statistic: {result[0]:.4f}')
    print(f'p-value: {result[1]:.4f}')
    print('Critical Values:')
    for key, value in result[4].items():
        print(f'   {key}: {value:.4f}')
    if result[1] <= 0.05:
        print("Conclusion: Reject null hypothesis - Series is stationary")
    else:
        print("Conclusion: Fail to reject null hypothesis - Series is non-stationary")

# Perform unit root tests
adf_test(nvda_prices, 'NVDA Price')
adf_test(msft_prices, 'MSFT Price')

# If non-stationary, take first differences
nvda_diff = nvda_prices.diff().dropna()
msft_diff = msft_prices.diff().dropna()

# Test stationarity of differences
adf_test(nvda_diff, 'NVDA Price (First Difference)')
adf_test(msft_diff, 'MSFT Price (First Difference)')

# Function to fit ARMA model and print summary
def fit_arma(series, order, title):
    try:
        model = ARIMA(series, order=order)
        results = model.fit()
        print(f'\nARMA Model Results for {title} (p,d,q) = {order}')
        print(results.summary())
        return results
    except:
        print(f"Error fitting ARMA model for {title}")
        return None

# Fit ARMA models (using ARMA(1,1) as example - adjust orders as needed)
nvda_arma = fit_arma(nvda_diff, (1,0,1), 'NVDA')
msft_arma = fit_arma(msft_diff, (1,0,1), 'MSFT')

# Cointegration test
def cointegration_test(series1, series2, title1, title2):
    score, p_value, _ = coint(series1, series2)
    print(f'\nCointegration Test between {title1} and {title2}')
    print(f'Cointegration test statistic: {score:.4f}')
    print(f'p-value: {p_value:.4f}')
    if p_value <= 0.05:
        print("Conclusion: Reject null hypothesis - Series are cointegrated")
    else:
        print("Conclusion: Fail to reject null hypothesis - Series are not cointegrated")

# Perform cointegration test
cointegration_test(nvda_prices, msft_prices, 'NVDA', 'MSFT')

# Plot the original prices
plt.figure(figsize=(12,6))
plt.plot(nvda_prices, label='NVDA Price')
plt.plot(msft_prices, label='MSFT Price')
plt.title('NVDA vs MSFT Prices')
plt.legend()
plt.show()

# Plot the differences
plt.figure(figsize=(12,6))
plt.plot(nvda_diff, label='NVDA Price Diff')
plt.plot(msft_diff, label='MSFT Price Diff')
plt.title('NVDA vs MSFT Price Differences')
plt.legend()
plt.show()

# Import additional required library
from statsmodels.graphics.tsaplots import plot_acf, plot_pacf

# Function to determine optimal ARIMA parameters using ACF/PACF
def plot_acf_pacf(series, title):
    plt.figure(figsize=(12,4))
    plt.subplot(121)
    plot_acf(series, ax=plt.gca())
    plt.title(f'ACF - {title}')
    plt.subplot(122)
    plot_pacf(series, ax=plt.gca())
    plt.title(f'PACF - {title}')
    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.show()

# Plot ACF and PACF for differenced series
plot_acf_pacf(nvda_diff, 'NVDA Differenced')
plot_acf_pacf(msft_diff, 'MSFT Differenced')

# Function to fit ARIMA model and forecast
def fit_arima_forecast(series, order, steps, title):
    try:
        # Fit ARIMA model
        model = ARIMA(series, order=order)
        results = model.fit()

        # Print model summary
        print(f'\nARIMA Model Results for {title} (p,d,q) = {order}')
        print(results.summary())

        # Forecast
        forecast = results.forecast(steps=steps)

        # Plot original series, fitted values, and forecast
        plt.figure(figsize=(12,6))
        plt.plot(series, label='Actual')
        plt.plot(results.fittedvalues, label='Fitted', alpha=0.7)
        forecast_index = pd.date_range(start=series.index[-1], periods=steps+1, freq='B')[1:]
        plt.plot(forecast_index, forecast, label='Forecast', color='red')
        plt.title(f'{title} - ARIMA{order} Forecast')
        plt.legend()
        plt.grid(True)
        plt.show()

        return results, forecast
    except:
        print(f"Error fitting ARIMA model for {title}")
        return None, None

# Set forecast horizon (e.g., 20 business days)
forecast_steps = 20

# If original series needed index, add it (assuming daily data)
nvda_prices.index = pd.date_range(start='2023-01-01', periods=len(nvda_prices), freq='B')
msft_prices.index = pd.date_range(start='2023-01-01', periods=len(msft_prices), freq='B')
nvda_diff.index = nvda_prices.index[1:]
msft_diff.index = msft_prices.index[1:]

# Fit ARIMA models and forecast
# Using ARIMA(1,1,1) as example - adjust based on ACF/PACF or AIC/BIC
nvda_arima, nvda_forecast = fit_arima_forecast(nvda_prices, (1,1,1), forecast_steps, 'NVDA')
msft_arima, msft_forecast = fit_arima_forecast(msft_prices, (1,1,1), forecast_steps, 'MSFT')

# Residual analysis
def plot_residuals(results, title):
    if results is not None:
        residuals = results.resid
        plt.figure(figsize=(12,6))
        plt.subplot(211)
        plt.plot(residuals)
        plt.title(f'{title} - Residuals')
        plt.subplot(212)
        plot_acf(residuals, ax=plt.gca())
        plt.title(f'{title} - Residuals ACF')
        plt.tight_layout()
        plt.show()

# Plot residuals
plot_residuals(nvda_arima, 'NVDA')
plot_residuals(msft_arima, 'MSFT')

# Re-run unit root tests on original series (already done in previous code, included for completeness)
print("\nRepeating Unit Root Tests for Reference:")
adf_test(nvda_prices, 'NVDA Price')
adf_test(msft_prices, 'MSFT Price')
adf_test(nvda_diff, 'NVDA Price (First Difference)')
adf_test(msft_diff, 'MSFT Price (First Difference)')

# Re-run cointegration test
cointegration_test(nvda_prices, msft_prices, 'NVDA', 'MSFT')

# Print forecast values
print(f'\nNVDA Forecast for next {forecast_steps} periods:')
print(nvda_forecast)
print(f'\nMSFT Forecast for next {forecast_steps} periods:')
print(msft_forecast)

# Continuing from previous codes - add this after the second code block

# Import additional libraries if needed
from statsmodels.tsa.stattools import acf, pacf

# Function to provide detailed interpretation of ADF test
def interpret_adf(result, title):
    print(f'\nInterpretation of ADF Test for {title}:')
    print(f'ADF Statistic: {result[0]:.4f}')
    print(f'p-value: {result[1]:.4f}')
    if result[1] <= 0.05:
        print("Interpretation: The series is stationary (rejects null hypothesis of unit root)")
        print("Implication: No differencing needed for stationarity")
    else:
        print("Interpretation: The series is non-stationary (fails to reject null hypothesis)")
        print("Implication: Differencing or transformation may be required")
    print("Critical Values Comparison:")
    for key, value in result[4].items():
        print(f'   {key}: {value:.4f} {"<" if result[0] < value else ">"} ADF Statistic ({result[0]:.4f})')

# Function to interpret ARIMA results and forecast
def interpret_arima(results, forecast, series, title, steps):
    if results is not None:
        print(f'\nInterpretation of ARIMA Model for {title}:')

        # Model fit statistics
        print(f'AIC: {results.aic:.2f} (Lower is better)')
        print(f'BIC: {results.bic:.2f} (Lower is better)')

        # Check parameter significance
        print("\nParameter Significance:")
        pvalues = results.pvalues
        for param, pval in pvalues.items():
            print(f'{param}: p-value = {pval:.4f} {"(Significant)" if pval < 0.05 else "(Not Significant)"}')

        # Residual diagnostics
        resid = results.resid
        ljung_box = sm.stats.acorr_ljungbox(resid, lags=[10], return_df=True)
        print(f'\nLjung-Box Test for Residual Autocorrelation (lag=10):')
        print(f'p-value: {ljung_box["lb_pvalue"].iloc[0]:.4f}')
        if ljung_box["lb_pvalue"].iloc[0] > 0.05:
            print("Interpretation: No significant autocorrelation in residuals (good fit)")
        else:
            print("Interpretation: Significant autocorrelation in residuals (model may need adjustment)")

        # Forecast interpretation
        last_value = series.iloc[-1]
        mean_forecast = forecast.mean()
        print(f'\nForecast Interpretation ({steps} steps):')
        print(f'Last observed value: {last_value:.2f}')
        print(f'Mean forecast value: {mean_forecast:.2f}')
        print(f'Forecast direction: {"Upward" if mean_forecast > last_value else "Downward"} trend')
        print(f'Forecast range: {forecast.min():.2f} to {forecast.max():.2f}')

# Function to interpret cointegration test
def interpret_coint(score, p_value, title1, title2):
    print(f'\nInterpretation of Cointegration Test between {title1} and {title2}:')
    print(f'Test Statistic: {score:.4f}')
    print(f'p-value: {p_value:.4f}')
    if p_value <= 0.05:
        print("Interpretation: Series are cointegrated (rejects null hypothesis)")
        print("Implication: Long-run equilibrium relationship exists between NVDA and MSFT prices")
    else:
        print("Interpretation: Series are not cointegrated (fails to reject null hypothesis)")
        print("Implication: No strong long-run relationship between NVDA and MSFT prices")

# Re-run and interpret ADF tests
print("\nDetailed Unit Root Test Interpretations:")
nvda_adf = adfuller(nvda_prices, autolag='AIC')
msft_adf = adfuller(msft_prices, autolag='AIC')
nvda_diff_adf = adfuller(nvda_diff, autolag='AIC')
msft_diff_adf = adfuller(msft_diff, autolag='AIC')

interpret_adf(nvda_adf, 'NVDA Price')
interpret_adf(msft_adf, 'MSFT Price')
interpret_adf(nvda_diff_adf, 'NVDA Price (First Difference)')
interpret_adf(msft_diff_adf, 'MSFT Price (First Difference)')

# Interpret ARIMA models and forecasts
interpret_arima(nvda_arima, nvda_forecast, nvda_prices, 'NVDA', forecast_steps)
interpret_arima(msft_arima, msft_forecast, msft_prices, 'MSFT', forecast_steps)

# Interpret cointegration test
coint_score, coint_pvalue, _ = coint(nvda_prices, msft_prices)
interpret_coint(coint_score, coint_pvalue, 'NVDA', 'MSFT')

# Enhanced forecast plots with confidence intervals
def plot_forecast_with_ci(results, series, steps, title):
    if results is not None:
        forecast_obj = results.get_forecast(steps=steps)
        forecast = forecast_obj.predicted_mean
        conf_int = forecast_obj.conf_int()

        plt.figure(figsize=(12,6))
        plt.plot(series[-50:], label='Actual (last 50 periods)')  # Show last 50 periods
        plt.plot(results.fittedvalues[-50:], label='Fitted', alpha=0.7)
        forecast_index = pd.date_range(start=series.index[-1], periods=steps+1, freq='B')[1:]
        plt.plot(forecast_index, forecast, label='Forecast', color='red')
        plt.fill_between(forecast_index,
                        conf_int.iloc[:,0],
                        conf_int.iloc[:,1],
                        color='pink',
                        alpha=0.3,
                        label='95% Confidence Interval')
        plt.title(f'{title} - ARIMA Forecast with Confidence Intervals')
        plt.legend()
        plt.grid(True)
        plt.show()

# Plot enhanced forecasts

# Function to perform ADF test
def adf_test(series, title=''):
    print(f'\nAugmented Dickey-Fuller Test: {title}')
    result = adfuller(series, autolag='AIC')
    print(f'ADF Statistic: {result[0]:.4f}')
    print(f'p-value: {result[1]:.4f}')
    print('Critical Values:')
    for key, value in result[4].items():
        print(f'   {key}: {value:.4f}')
    if result[1] <= 0.05:
        print("Conclusion: Reject null hypothesis - Series is stationary")
    else:
        print("Conclusion: Fail to reject null hypothesis - Series is non-stationary")

# Perform unit root tests
adf_test(goog_prices, 'GOOG Price')
adf_test(msft_prices, 'MSFT Price')

# Take first differences if non-stationary
goog_diff = goog_prices.diff().dropna()
msft_diff = msft_prices.diff().dropna()

# Test stationarity of differences
adf_test(goog_diff, 'GOOG Price (First Difference)')
adf_test(msft_diff, 'MSFT Price (First Difference)')

# Function to fit ARMA model and print summary
def fit_arma(series, order, title):
    try:
        model = ARIMA(series, order=order)
        results = model.fit()
        print(f'\nARMA Model Results for {title} (p,d,q) = {order}')
        print(results.summary())
        return results
    except:
        print(f"Error fitting ARMA model for {title}")
        return None

# Cointegration test
def cointegration_test(series1, series2, title1, title2):
    score, p_value, _ = coint(series1, series2)
    print(f'\nCointegration Test between {title1} and {title2}')
    print(f'Cointegration test statistic: {score:.4f}')
    print(f'p-value: {p_value:.4f}')
    if p_value <= 0.05:
        print("Conclusion: Reject null hypothesis - Series are cointegrated")
    else:
        print("Conclusion: Fail to reject null hypothesis - Series are not cointegrated")

# Function to fit ARIMA model and forecast
def fit_arima_forecast(series, order, steps, title):
    try:
        # Fit ARIMA model
        model = ARIMA(series, order=order)
        results = model.fit()

        # Print model summary
        print(f'\nARIMA Model Results for {title} (p,d,q) = {order}')
        print(results.summary())

        # Forecast
        forecast = results.forecast(steps=steps)

        # Plot original series, fitted values, and forecast
        plt.figure(figsize=(12,6))
        plt.plot(series, label='Actual')
        plt.plot(results.fittedvalues, label='Fitted', alpha=0.7)
        forecast_index = pd.RangeIndex(start=len(series), stop=len(series)+steps)
        plt.plot(forecast_index, forecast, label='Forecast', color='red')
        plt.title(f'{title} - ARIMA{order} Forecast')
        plt.legend()
        plt.grid(True)
        plt.show()

        return results, forecast
    except:
        print(f"Error fitting ARIMA model for {title}")
        return None, None

# Continuing from previous codes - add this after the second code block

# Import additional libraries if needed
from statsmodels.tsa.stattools import acf, pacf

# Function to provide detailed interpretation of ADF test
def interpret_adf(result, title):
    print(f'\nInterpretation of ADF Test for {title}:')
    print(f'ADF Statistic: {result[0]:.4f}')
    print(f'p-value: {result[1]:.4f}')
    if result[1] <= 0.05:
        print("Interpretation: The series is stationary (rejects null hypothesis of unit root)")
        print("Implication: No differencing needed for stationarity")
    else:
        print("Interpretation: The series is non-stationary (fails to reject null hypothesis)")
        print("Implication: Differencing or transformation may be required")
    print("Critical Values Comparison:")
    for key, value in result[4].items():
        print(f'   {key}: {value:.4f} {"<" if result[0] < value else ">"} ADF Statistic ({result[0]:.4f})')

# Function to interpret ARIMA results and forecast
def interpret_arima(results, forecast, series, title, steps):
    if results is not None:
        print(f'\nInterpretation of ARIMA Model for {title}:')

        # Model fit statistics
        print(f'AIC: {results.aic:.2f} (Lower is better)')
        print(f'BIC: {results.bic:.2f} (Lower is better)')

        # Check parameter significance
        print("\nParameter Significance:")
        pvalues = results.pvalues
        for param, pval in pvalues.items():
            print(f'{param}: p-value = {pval:.4f} {"(Significant)" if pval < 0.05 else "(Not Significant)"}')

        # Residual diagnostics
        resid = results.resid
        ljung_box = sm.stats.acorr_ljungbox(resid, lags=[10], return_df=True)
        print(f'\nLjung-Box Test for Residual Autocorrelation (lag=10):')
        print(f'p-value: {ljung_box["lb_pvalue"].iloc[0]:.4f}')
        if ljung_box["lb_pvalue"].iloc[0] > 0.05:
            print("Interpretation: No significant autocorrelation in residuals (good fit)")
        else:
            print("Interpretation: Significant autocorrelation in residuals (model may need adjustment)")

        # Forecast interpretation
        last_value = series.iloc[-1]
        mean_forecast = forecast.mean()
        print(f'\nForecast Interpretation ({steps} steps):')
        print(f'Last observed value: {last_value:.2f}')
        print(f'Mean forecast value: {mean_forecast:.2f}')
        print(f'Forecast direction: {"Upward" if mean_forecast > last_value else "Downward"} trend')
        print(f'Forecast range: {forecast.min():.2f} to {forecast.max():.2f}')

# Function to interpret cointegration test
def interpret_coint(score, p_value, title1, title2):
    print(f'\nInterpretation of Cointegration Test between {title1} and {title2}:')
    print(f'Test Statistic: {score:.4f}')
    print(f'p-value: {p_value:.4f}')
    if p_value <= 0.05:
        print("Interpretation: Series are cointegrated (rejects null hypothesis)")
        print("Implication: Long-run equilibrium relationship exists between GOOG and MSFT prices")
    else:
        print("Interpretation: Series are not cointegrated (fails to reject null hypothesis)")
        print("Implication: No strong long-run relationship between GOOG and MSFT prices")

# Re-run and interpret ADF tests
print("\nDetailed Unit Root Test Interpretations:")
goog_adf = adfuller(goog_prices, autolag='AIC')
msft_adf = adfuller(msft_prices, autolag='AIC')
goog_diff_adf = adfuller(goog_diff, autolag='AIC')

def plot_forecast_with_ci(results, series, steps, title):
    if results is not None:
        forecast_obj = results.get_forecast(steps=steps)
        forecast = forecast_obj.predicted_mean
        conf_int = forecast_obj.conf_int()

        plt.figure(figsize=(12,6))

        plt.plot(forecast_index, forecast, label='Forecast', color='red')
        plt.fill_between(forecast_index,
                        conf_int.iloc[:,0],
                        conf_int.iloc[:,1],
                        color='pink',
                        alpha=0.3,
                        label='95% Confidence Interval')
        plt.title(f'{title} - ARIMA Forecast with Confidence Intervals')
        plt.legend()
        plt.grid(True)
        plt.show()

# Plot enhanced forecasts

# Drop any NaN values
goog_prices = goog_prices.dropna()
nvda_prices = nvda_prices.dropna()

# Function to perform ADF test
def adf_test(series, title=''):
    print(f'\nAugmented Dickey-Fuller Test: {title}')
    result = adfuller(series, autolag='AIC')
    print(f'ADF Statistic: {result[0]:.4f}')
    print(f'p-value: {result[1]:.4f}')
    print('Critical Values:')
    for key, value in result[4].items():
        print(f'   {key}: {value:.4f}')
    if result[1] <= 0.05:
        print("Conclusion: Reject null hypothesis - Series is stationary")
    else:
        print("Conclusion: Fail to reject null hypothesis - Series is non-stationary")

# Perform unit root tests
adf_test(goog_prices, 'GOOG Price')
adf_test(nvda_prices, 'NVDA Price')

# Take first differences if non-stationary
goog_diff = goog_prices.diff().dropna()
nvda_diff = nvda_prices.diff().dropna()

# Test stationarity of differences
adf_test(goog_diff, 'GOOG Price (First Difference)')
adf_test(nvda_diff, 'NVDA Price (First Difference)')

# Function to fit ARMA model and print summary
def fit_arma(series, order, title):
    try:
        model = ARIMA(series, order=order)
        results = model.fit()
        print(f'\nARMA Model Results for {title} (p,d,q) = {order}')
        print(results.summary())
        return results
    except:
        print(f"Error fitting ARMA model for {title}")
        return None

# Fit ARMA models (using ARMA(1,0,1) as example - adjust orders as needed)

nvda_arma = fit_arma(nvda_diff, (1,0,1), 'NVDA')

# Cointegration test
def cointegration_test(series1, series2, title1, title2):
    score, p_value, _ = coint(series1, series2)
    print(f'\nCointegration Test between {title1} and {title2}')
    print(f'Cointegration test statistic: {score:.4f}')
    print(f'p-value: {p_value:.4f}')
    if p_value <= 0.05:
        print("Conclusion: Reject null hypothesis - Series are cointegrated")
    else:
        print("Conclusion: Fail to reject null hypothesis - Series are not cointegrated")

# Perform cointegration test

# Function to fit ARIMA model and forecast
def fit_arima_forecast(series, order, steps, title):
    try:
        # Fit ARIMA model
        model = ARIMA(series, order=order)
        results = model.fit()

        # Print model summary
        print(f'\nARIMA Model Results for {title} (p,d,q) = {order}')
        print(results.summary())

        # Forecast
        forecast = results.forecast(steps=steps)

        # Plot original series, fitted values, and forecast
        plt.figure(figsize=(12,6))
        plt.plot(series, label='Actual')
        plt.plot(results.fittedvalues, label='Fitted', alpha=0.7)
        forecast_index = pd.RangeIndex(start=len(series), stop=len(series)+steps)
        plt.plot(forecast_index, forecast, label='Forecast', color='red')
        plt.title(f'{title} - ARIMA{order} Forecast')
        plt.legend()
        plt.grid(True)
        plt.show()

        return results, forecast
    except:
        print(f"Error fitting ARIMA model for {title}")
        return None, None

# Function to provide detailed interpretation of ADF test
def interpret_adf(result, title):
    print(f'\nInterpretation of ADF Test for {title}:')
    print(f'ADF Statistic: {result[0]:.4f}')
    print(f'p-value: {result[1]:.4f}')
    if result[1] <= 0.05:
        print("Interpretation: The series is stationary (rejects null hypothesis of unit root)")
        print("Implication: No differencing needed for stationarity")
    else:
        print("Interpretation: The series is non-stationary (fails to reject null hypothesis)")
        print("Implication: Differencing or transformation may be required")
    print("Critical Values Comparison:")
    for key, value in result[4].items():
        print(f'   {key}: {value:.4f} {"<" if result[0] < value else ">"} ADF Statistic ({result[0]:.4f})')

# Function to interpret ARIMA results and forecast
def interpret_arima(results, forecast, series, title, steps):
    if results is not None:
        print(f'\nInterpretation of ARIMA Model for {title}:')

        # Model fit statistics
        print(f'AIC: {results.aic:.2f} (Lower is better)')
        print(f'BIC: {results.bic:.2f} (Lower is better)')

        # Check parameter significance
        print("\nParameter Significance:")
        pvalues = results.pvalues
        for param, pval in pvalues.items():
            print(f'{param}: p-value = {pval:.4f} {"(Significant)" if pval < 0.05 else "(Not Significant)"}')

        # Residual diagnostics
        resid = results.resid
        ljung_box = sm.stats.acorr_ljungbox(resid, lags=[10], return_df=True)
        print(f'\nLjung-Box Test for Residual Autocorrelation (lag=10):')
        print(f'p-value: {ljung_box["lb_pvalue"].iloc[0]:.4f}')
        if ljung_box["lb_pvalue"].iloc[0] > 0.05:
            print("Interpretation: No significant autocorrelation in residuals (good fit)")
        else:
            print("Interpretation: Significant autocorrelation in residuals (model may need adjustment)")

        # Forecast interpretation
        last_value = series.iloc[-1]
        mean_forecast = forecast.mean()
        print(f'\nForecast Interpretation ({steps} steps):')
        print(f'Last observed value: {last_value:.2f}')
        print(f'Mean forecast value: {mean_forecast:.2f}')
        print(f'Forecast direction: {"Upward" if mean_forecast > last_value else "Downward"} trend')
        print(f'Forecast range: {forecast.min():.2f} to {forecast.max():.2f}')

# Function to interpret cointegration test
def interpret_coint(score, p_value, title1, title2):
    print(f'\nInterpretation of Cointegration Test between {title1} and {title2}:')
    print(f'Test Statistic: {score:.4f}')
    print(f'p-value: {p_value:.4f}')
    if p_value <= 0.05:
        print("Interpretation: Series are cointegrated (rejects null hypothesis)")
        print("Implication: Long-run equilibrium relationship exists between GOOG and NVDA prices")
    else:
        print("Interpretation: Series are not cointegrated (fails to reject null hypothesis)")
        print("Implication: No strong long-run relationship between GOOG and NVDA prices")

def plot_forecast_with_ci(results, series, steps, title):

        plt.plot(forecast_index, forecast, label='Forecast', color='red')
        plt.fill_between(forecast_index,
                        conf_int.iloc[:,0],
                        conf_int.iloc[:,1],
                        color='pink',
                        alpha=0.3,
                        label='95% Confidence Interval')
        plt.title(f'{title} - ARIMA Forecast with Confidence Intervals')
        plt.legend()
        plt.grid(True)
        plt.show()

# Function to perform ADF test
def adf_test(series, title=''):
    print(f'\nAugmented Dickey-Fuller Test: {title}')
    result = adfuller(series, autolag='AIC')
    print(f'ADF Statistic: {result[0]:.4f}')
    print(f'p-value: {result[1]:.4f}')
    print('Critical Values:')
    for key, value in result[4].items():
        print(f'   {key}: {value:.4f}')
    if result[1] <= 0.05:
        print("Conclusion: Reject null hypothesis - Series is stationary")
    else:
        print("Conclusion: Fail to reject null hypothesis - Series is non-stationary")

# Perform unit root tests
adf_test(nvdaa_prices, 'NVDAA Price')
adf_test(msftt_prices, 'MSFTT Price')

# Take first differences if non-stationary
nvdaa_diff = nvdaa_prices.diff().dropna()
msftt_diff = msftt_prices.diff().dropna()

# Test stationarity of differences
adf_test(nvdaa_diff, 'NVDAA Price (First Difference)')
adf_test(msftt_diff, 'MSFTT Price (First Difference)')

# Function to fit ARMA model and print summary
def fit_arma(series, order, title):
    try:
        model = ARIMA(series, order=order)
        results = model.fit()
        print(f'\nARMA Model Results for {title} (p,d,q) = {order}')
        print(results.summary())
        return results
    except:
        print(f"Error fitting ARMA model for {title}")
        return None

# Cointegration test
def cointegration_test(series1, series2, title1, title2):
    score, p_value, _ = coint(series1, series2)
    print(f'\nCointegration Test between {title1} and {title2}')
    print(f'Cointegration test statistic: {score:.4f}')
    print(f'p-value: {p_value:.4f}')
    if p_value <= 0.05:
        print("Conclusion: Reject null hypothesis - Series are cointegrated")
    else:
        print("Conclusion: Fail to reject null hypothesis - Series are not cointegrated")

# Function to plot ACF and PACF for order selection
def plot_acf_pacf(series, title):
    plt.figure(figsize=(12,4))
    plt.subplot(121)
    plot_acf(series, ax=plt.gca())
    plt.title(f'ACF - {title}')
    plt.subplot(122)

    plt.title(f'PACF - {title}')
    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.show()

# Function to fit ARIMA model and forecast
def fit_arima_forecast(series, order, steps, title):
    try:
        # Fit ARIMA model
        model = ARIMA(series, order=order)
        results = model.fit()

        # Print model summary
        print(f'\nARIMA Model Results for {title} (p,d,q) = {order}')
        print(results.summary())

        # Forecast
        forecast = results.forecast(steps=steps)

        # Plot original series, fitted values, and forecast
        plt.figure(figsize=(12,6))
        plt.plot(series, label='Actual')
        plt.plot(results.fittedvalues, label='Fitted', alpha=0.7)
        forecast_index = pd.RangeIndex(start=len(series), stop=len(series)+steps)
        plt.plot(forecast_index, forecast, label='Forecast', color='red')
        plt.title(f'{title} - ARIMA{order} Forecast')
        plt.legend()
        plt.grid(True)
        plt.show()

        return results, forecast
    except:
        print(f"Error fitting ARIMA model for {title}")
        return None, None

msftt_prices.index = pd.date_range(start='2023-01-01', periods=len(msftt_prices), freq='B')
nvdaa_diff.index = nvdaa_prices.index[1:]
msftt_diff.index = msftt_prices.index[1:]

# Function to provide detailed interpretation of ADF test
def interpret_adf(result, title):
    print(f'\nInterpretation of ADF Test for {title}:')
    print(f'ADF Statistic: {result[0]:.4f}')
    print(f'p-value: {result[1]:.4f}')
    if result[1] <= 0.05:
        print("Interpretation: The series is stationary (rejects null hypothesis of unit root)")
        print("Implication: No differencing needed for stationarity")
    else:
        print("Interpretation: The series is non-stationary (fails to reject null hypothesis)")
        print("Implication: Differencing or transformation may be required")
    print("Critical Values Comparison:")
    for key, value in result[4].items():
        print(f'   {key}: {value:.4f} {"<" if result[0] < value else ">"} ADF Statistic ({result[0]:.4f})')

# Function to interpret ARIMA results and forecast
def interpret_arima(results, forecast, series, title, steps):
    if results is not None:
        print(f'\nInterpretation of ARIMA Model for {title}:')

        # Model fit statistics
        print(f'AIC: {results.aic:.2f} (Lower is better)')
        print(f'BIC: {results.bic:.2f} (Lower is better)')

        # Check parameter significance
        print("\nParameter Significance:")
        pvalues = results.pvalues
        for param, pval in pvalues.items():
            print(f'{param}: p-value = {pval:.4f} {"(Significant)" if pval < 0.05 else "(Not Significant)"}')

        # Residual diagnostics
        resid = results.resid
        ljung_box = sm.stats.acorr_ljungbox(resid, lags=[10], return_df=True)
        print(f'\nLjung-Box Test for Residual Autocorrelation (lag=10):')
        print(f'p-value: {ljung_box["lb_pvalue"].iloc[0]:.4f}')
        if ljung_box["lb_pvalue"].iloc[0] > 0.05:
            print("Interpretation: No significant autocorrelation in residuals (good fit)")
        else:
            print("Interpretation: Significant autocorrelation in residuals (model may need adjustment)")

        # Forecast interpretation
        last_value = series.iloc[-1]
        mean_forecast = forecast.mean()
        print(f'\nForecast Interpretation ({steps} steps):')
        print(f'Last observed value: {last_value:.2f}')
        print(f'Mean forecast value: {mean_forecast:.2f}')
        print(f'Forecast direction: {"Upward" if mean_forecast > last_value else "Downward"} trend')
        print(f'Forecast range: {forecast.min():.2f} to {forecast.max():.2f}')

# Function to interpret cointegration test
def interpret_coint(score, p_value, title1, title2):
    print(f'\nInterpretation of Cointegration Test between {title1} and {title2}:')
    print(f'Test Statistic: {score:.4f}')
    print(f'p-value: {p_value:.4f}')
    if p_value <= 0.05:
        print("Interpretation: Series are cointegrated (rejects null hypothesis)")
        print("Implication: Long-run equilibrium relationship exists between NVDAA and MSFTT prices")
    else:
        print("Interpretation: Series are not cointegrated (fails to reject null hypothesis)")
        print("Implication: No strong long-run relationship between NVDAA and MSFTT prices")

# Enhanced forecast plots with confidence intervals
def plot_forecast_with_ci(results, series, steps, title):
    if results is not None:
        forecast_obj = results.get_forecast(steps=steps)
        forecast = forecast_obj.predicted_mean
        conf_int = forecast_obj.conf_int()

        plt.figure(figsize=(12,6))
        plt.plot(series[-50:], label='Actual (last 50 periods)')  # Show last 50 periods
        plt.plot(results.fittedvalues[-50:], label='Fitted', alpha=0.7)
        forecast_index = pd.date_range(start=series.index[-1], periods=steps+1, freq='B')[1:]
        plt.plot(forecast_index, forecast, label='Forecast', color='red')
        plt.fill_between(forecast_index,
                        conf_int.iloc[:,0],
                        conf_int.iloc[:,1],
                        color='pink',
                        alpha=0.3,
                        label='95% Confidence Interval')
        plt.title(f'{title} - ARIMA Forecast with Confidence Intervals')
        plt.legend()
        plt.grid(True)
        plt.show()

# Function to perform ADF test
def adf_test(series, title=''):
    print(f'\nAugmented Dickey-Fuller Test: {title}')
    result = adfuller(series, autolag='AIC')
    print(f'ADF Statistic: {result[0]:.4f}')
    print(f'p-value: {result[1]:.4f}')
    print('Critical Values:')
    for key, value in result[4].items():
        print(f'   {key}: {value:.4f}')
    if result[1] <= 0.05:
        print("Conclusion: Reject null hypothesis - Series is stationary")
    else:
        print("Conclusion: Fail to reject null hypothesis - Series is non-stationary")

# Perform unit root tests
adf_test(goog_prices, 'GOOGG Price')
adf_test(msft_prices, 'MSFTT Price')

# Take first differences if non-stationary
goog_diff = goog_prices.diff().dropna()
msft_diff = msft_prices.diff().dropna()

# Test stationarity of differences
adf_test(goog_diff, 'GOOGG Price (First Difference)')
adf_test(msft_diff, 'MSFTT Price (First Difference)')

# Function to fit ARMA model and print summary
def fit_arma(series, order, title):
    try:
        model = ARIMA(series, order=order)
        results = model.fit()
        print(f'\nARMA Model Results for {title} (p,d,q) = {order}')
        print(results.summary())
        return results
    except:
        print(f"Error fitting ARMA model for {title}")
        return None

# Cointegration test
def cointegration_test(series1, series2, title1, title2):
    score, p_value, _ = coint(series1, series2)
    print(f'\nCointegration Test between {title1} and {title2}')
    print(f'Cointegration test statistic: {score:.4f}')
    print(f'p-value: {p_value:.4f}')
    if p_value <= 0.05:
        print("Conclusion: Reject null hypothesis - Series are cointegrated")
    else:
        print("Conclusion: Fail to reject null hypothesis - Series are not cointegrated")

# Function to plot ACF and PACF for order selection
def plot_acf_pacf(series, title):
    plt.figure(figsize=(12,4))
    plt.subplot(121)
    plot_acf(series, ax=plt.gca())
    plt.title(f'ACF - {title}')

    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.show()

# Function to fit ARIMA model and forecast
def fit_arima_forecast(series, order, steps, title):
    try:
        # Fit ARIMA model
        model = ARIMA(series, order=order)
        results = model.fit()

        # Print model summary
        print(f'\nARIMA Model Results for {title} (p,d,q) = {order}')
        print(results.summary())

        # Forecast
        forecast = results.forecast(steps=steps)

        # Plot original series, fitted values, and forecast
        plt.figure(figsize=(12,6))
        plt.plot(series, label='Actual')
        plt.plot(results.fittedvalues, label='Fitted', alpha=0.7)
        forecast_index = pd.date_range(start=series.index[-1], periods=steps+1, freq='B')[1:]
        plt.plot(forecast_index, forecast, label='Forecast', color='red')
        plt.title(f'{title} - ARIMA{order} Forecast')
        plt.legend()
        plt.grid(True)
        plt.show()

        return results, forecast
    except:
        print(f"Error fitting ARIMA model for {title}")
        return None, None

# Function to provide detailed interpretation of ADF test
def interpret_adf(result, title):
    print(f'\nInterpretation of ADF Test for {title}:')
    print(f'ADF Statistic: {result[0]:.4f}')
    print(f'p-value: {result[1]:.4f}')
    if result[1] <= 0.05:
        print("Interpretation: The series is stationary (rejects null hypothesis of unit root)")
        print("Implication: No differencing needed for stationarity")
    else:
        print("Interpretation: The series is non-stationary (fails to reject null hypothesis)")
        print("Implication: Differencing or transformation may be required")
    print("Critical Values Comparison:")
    for key, value in result[4].items():
        print(f'   {key}: {value:.4f} {"<" if result[0] < value else ">"} ADF Statistic ({result[0]:.4f})')

# Function to interpret ARIMA results and forecast
def interpret_arima(results, forecast, series, title, steps):
    if results is not None:
        print(f'\nInterpretation of ARIMA Model for {title}:')

        # Model fit statistics
        print(f'AIC: {results.aic:.2f} (Lower is better)')
        print(f'BIC: {results.bic:.2f} (Lower is better)')

        # Check parameter significance
        print("\nParameter Significance:")
        pvalues = results.pvalues
        for param, pval in pvalues.items():
            print(f'{param}: p-value = {pval:.4f} {"(Significant)" if pval < 0.05 else "(Not Significant)"}')

        # Residual diagnostics
        resid = results.resid
        ljung_box = sm.stats.acorr_ljungbox(resid, lags=[10], return_df=True)
        print(f'\nLjung-Box Test for Residual Autocorrelation (lag=10):')
        print(f'p-value: {ljung_box["lb_pvalue"].iloc[0]:.4f}')
        if ljung_box["lb_pvalue"].iloc[0] > 0.05:
            print("Interpretation: No significant autocorrelation in residuals (good fit)")
        else:
            print("Interpretation: Significant autocorrelation in residuals (model may need adjustment)")

        # Forecast interpretation
        last_value = series.iloc[-1]
        mean_forecast = forecast.mean()
        print(f'\nForecast Interpretation ({steps} steps):')
        print(f'Last observed value: {last_value:.2f}')
        print(f'Mean forecast value: {mean_forecast:.2f}')
        print(f'Forecast direction: {"Upward" if mean_forecast > last_value else "Downward"} trend')
        print(f'Forecast range: {forecast.min():.2f} to {forecast.max():.2f}')

# Function to interpret cointegration test
def interpret_coint(score, p_value, title1, title2):
    print(f'\nInterpretation of Cointegration Test between {title1} and {title2}:')
    print(f'Test Statistic: {score:.4f}')
    print(f'p-value: {p_value:.4f}')
    if p_value <= 0.05:
        print("Interpretation: Series are cointegrated (rejects null hypothesis)")
        print("Implication: Long-run equilibrium relationship exists between GOOGG and MSFTT prices")
    else:
        print("Interpretation: Series are not cointegrated (fails to reject null hypothesis)")
        print("Implication: No strong long-run relationship between GOOGG and MSFTT prices")

# Enhanced forecast plots with confidence intervals
def plot_forecast_with_ci(results, series, steps, title):
    if results is not None:
        forecast_obj = results.get_forecast(steps=steps)
        forecast = forecast_obj.predicted_mean

        plt.fill_between(forecast_index,
                        conf_int.iloc[:,0],

                        alpha=0.3,
                        label='95% Confidence Interval')
        plt.title(f'{title} - ARIMA Forecast with Confidence Intervals')
        plt.legend()

        plt.show()

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# Upload files
print("Please upload GOOGG.xlsx")
uploaded_goog = files.upload()
print("Please upload NVDAA.xlsx")
uploaded_nvda = files.upload()

# Read Excel files
goog_df = pd.read_excel('GOOGG.xlsx')
nvda_df = pd.read_excel('NVDAA.xlsx')

# Print column names for debugging
print("\nGOOGG.xlsx columns:", goog_df.columns.tolist())
print("NVDAA.xlsx columns:", nvda_df.columns.tolist())

# Specify the price column names for each file
goog_price_column = 'PRICE'   # Assuming this for GOOGG
nvda_price_column = 'PRICE '  # Confirmed for NVDAA with trailing space

# Check if the specified columns exist
if goog_price_column not in goog_df.columns:
    raise KeyError(f"'{goog_price_column}' not found in GOOGG.xlsx. Available columns: {goog_df.columns.tolist()}")
if nvda_price_column not in nvda_df.columns:
    raise KeyError(f"'{nvda_price_column}' not found in NVDAA.xlsx. Available columns: {nvda_df.columns.tolist()}")

# Extract PRICE columns and ensure they're numeric
goog_prices = pd.to_numeric(goog_df[goog_price_column], errors='coerce')
nvda_prices = pd.to_numeric(nvda_df[nvda_price_column], errors='coerce')

# Drop any NaN values
goog_prices = goog_prices.dropna()
nvda_prices = nvda_prices.dropna()

# Function to perform ADF test
def adf_test(series, title=''):
    print(f'\nAugmented Dickey-Fuller Test: {title}')
    result = adfuller(series, autolag='AIC')
    print(f'ADF Statistic: {result[0]:.4f}')
    print(f'p-value: {result[1]:.4f}')
    print('Critical Values:')
    for key, value in result[4].items():
        print(f'   {key}: {value:.4f}')
    if result[1] <= 0.05:
        print("Conclusion: Reject null hypothesis - Series is stationary")
    else:
        print("Conclusion: Fail to reject null hypothesis - Series is non-stationary")

# Perform unit root tests
adf_test(goog_prices, 'GOOGG Price')
adf_test(nvda_prices, 'NVDAA Price')

# Take first differences if non-stationary
goog_diff = goog_prices.diff().dropna()
nvda_diff = nvda_prices.diff().dropna()

# Test stationarity of differences
adf_test(goog_diff, 'GOOGG Price (First Difference)')
adf_test(nvda_diff, 'NVDAA Price (First Difference)')

# Function to fit ARMA model and print summary
def fit_arma(series, order, title):
    try:
        model = ARIMA(series, order=order)
        results = model.fit()
        print(f'\nARMA Model Results for {title} (p,d,q) = {order}')
        print(results.summary())
        return results
    except:
        print(f"Error fitting ARMA model for {title}")
        return None

# Fit ARMA models (using ARMA(1,0,1) as example - adjust orders as needed)
goog_arma = fit_arma(goog_diff, (1,0,1), 'GOOGG')
nvda_arma = fit_arma(nvda_diff, (1,0,1), 'NVDAA')

# Cointegration test
def cointegration_test(series1, series2, title1, title2):
    score, p_value, _ = coint(series1, series2)
    print(f'\nCointegration Test between {title1} and {title2}')
    print(f'Cointegration test statistic: {score:.4f}')
    print(f'p-value: {p_value:.4f}')
    if p_value <= 0.05:
        print("Conclusion: Reject null hypothesis - Series are cointegrated")
    else:
        print("Conclusion: Fail to reject null hypothesis - Series are not cointegrated")

# Perform cointegration test
cointegration_test(goog_prices, nvda_prices, 'GOOGG', 'NVDAA')

import pandas as pd

from google.colab import files
import statsmodels.api as sm
from statsmodels.tsa.stattools import adfuller, coint
from statsmodels.tsa.arima.model import ARIMA

# Upload files
print("Please upload NVDAA.xlsx")
uploaded_nvdaa = files.upload()
print("Please upload GOOGG.xlsx")

# Extract PRICE columns
nvdaa_price = nvdaa['PRICE']
googg_price = googg['PRICE']

# Function for ADF test (unit root test)
def adf_test(series, title=''):
    print(f'\nAugmented Dickey-Fuller Test: {title}')
    result = adfuller(series.dropna())
    print(f'ADF Statistic: {result[0]}')
    print(f'p-value: {result[1]}')
    print('Critical Values:')
    for key, value in result[4].items():
        print(f'   {key}: {value}')
    if result[1] <= 0.05:
        print("Strong evidence against null hypothesis - Stationary")
    else:
        print("Weak evidence against null hypothesis - Non-stationary")

# Perform ADF test on original series
adf_test(nvdaa_price, 'NVDAA Price')
adf_test(googg_price, 'GOOGG Price')

# If non-stationary, take first differences
nvdaa_diff = nvdaa_price.diff().dropna()
googg_diff = googg_price.diff().dropna()

# Perform ADF test on differenced series
adf_test(nvdaa_diff, 'NVDAA Price (First Difference)')
adf_test(googg_diff, 'GOOGG Price (First Difference)')

# ARMA model function
def fit_arma(series, order, title=''):
    model = ARIMA(series, order=order)
    results = model.fit()
    print(f'\nARMA Model Results: {title}')
    print(results.summary())
    return results

# Fit ARMA models (using ARMA(1,1) as example - adjust orders as needed)
nvdaa_arma = fit_arma(nvdaa_diff, (1,0,1), 'NVDAA Differenced')
googg_arma = fit_arma(googg_diff, (1,0,1), 'GOOGG Differenced')

# Plot residuals

plt.subplot(121)

plt.subplot(122)

plt.title('GOOGG ARMA Residuals')
